                                    java.lang.String street,

                                    java.lang.String state,
                                    java.lang.String zip)
        Connects to the MySQL server and updates an address with a user inputed id and checks to make sure that the new address doesn't already exist in the database. If successful at updating the address the new address will be returned
        Parameters:
        conn - The MySQL connection
        id - The ID of the address to update
        number - The new number of the address to be updated blank if keeping the old number
        street - The new street of the address to be updated blank if keeping the old street
        city - The new city of the address to be updated blank if keeping the old city
        state - The new stare of the address to be updated blank if keeping the old state
        zip - The new zip of the address to be updated blank if keeping the old zip
        Returns:
        The updated address if successful if not null is returned
